    "Id": "191903",
    "ThreadId": "56778",
    "Html": "<p>Are there any guidelines for a region to view ratio? In other words, is it best to have one view per region or we can have more (say 5 or 10).</p>\r\n<p>Would it just depend on our application and our requirements?</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-19T06:38:38.237-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "191905",
    "ThreadId": "56778",
    "Html": "<p>That depends. If your region is like a Selector control (Tab control), then you can have as many views as possible. For a Content or Items region, I think you can have only one view per region.</p>\r\n<p>Hope it's right and answers your query.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-19T06:41:58.413-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "192387",
    "ThreadId": "56778",
    "Html": "<p>Thanks Osei.</p>\r\n<p>Im adding a collection of views to a listbox. This list box is inside a region. Would this scenario be valid?</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-20T07:47:19.027-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "192467",
    "ThreadId": "56778",
    "Html": "<p>I don't quite understand your scenario but I would suggest looking into scoped regions. Are you displaying the views inside the listbox? Are the number of views known at design time or dynamic at run-time??</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-20T10:40:34.817-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
  {
    "Id": "192503",
    "ThreadId": "56778",
    "Html": "<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Hi winrunner, </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">A couple of days ago there was a discussion tightly related to this topic. Perhaps you could find it enriching:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt;text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://compositewpf.codeplex.com/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=56692\"><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">Best way to manage views in a region&nbsp; </span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\" lang=EN-US>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">As you are adding view to a listbox (adapted by prism by the <strong>SelectorRegionAdapter</strong><span style=\"\">),</span> when you add a view to the region, it will be added as an item to the listbox. So in this scenario it makes sense to have several views in the same region.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"color:#003300\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"color:#003300\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">Keep in mind that if other modules won't add views to the region, you might not even need to attach a region to the listbox. As Osei said, </span><a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dd458914.aspx\"><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">scoped regions</span></a><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\"> might be a good option in some </span></span><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">scenarios. These are some discussions related to these topic:<span style=\"color:#003300\"></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt;text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"color:#003300;font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"color:#003300\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://compositewpf.codeplex.com/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=52480\"><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">Multiple Views</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt;text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"color:#003300;font-family:Symbol\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:small\">&middot;</span><span style=\"font:7pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"color:#003300\" lang=EN-US><a href=\"http://compositewpf.codeplex.com/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=51525\"><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">Architecture of sub controls in regions</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><strong><em><span style=\"color:#003300\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></em></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Hope it helps!</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri\">Matias Bonaventura</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0pt\"><a href=\"http://blogs.southworks.net/\"><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US><span style=\"font-size:small;font-family:Calibri\">http://blogs.southworks.net/matiasb</span></span></a><span style=\"\" lang=EN-US></span></p>",
